        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " would take place, \"write you this song.\" \"This\" refers to the song which follows in ch. 32. Moses and Joshua were to write the song, because they were both of them to strive to prevent the apostasy of the people; and Moses, as the author, was to teach it to the children of Israel, to make them learn it, that it might be a witness for the Lord (for Me) against the children of Israel. \"This\" is defined still further in ",
        "children": []
