        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " : if Israel, through growing satisfied and fat in its land, which was so rich in costly good, should turn to other gods, and the Lord should visit it in consequence with grievous evils and troubles, the song was to answer before Israel as a witness; i.e., not only serve the Lord as a witness to the people that He had foretold all the evil consequences of apostasy, and had given Israel proper warning (Knobel), but to serve, as we may see from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
